<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="460" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,717]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,655,680]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet “ 
<taxonomicName box="[591,695,656,680]" class="Insecta" family="Pterophoridae" genus="Platyptilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mugesse">Mugesse</taxonomicName>
” is a toponymic name, referring to the 
<typeStatus box="[1159,1207,656,680]" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">type</typeStatus>
locality of the new species in the 
<taxonomicName box="[309,409,693,717]" class="Insecta" family="Pterophoridae" genus="Platyptilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="460" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mugesse">Mugesse</taxonomicName>
forest in the north of 
<collectingCountry box="[652,741,692,717]" name="Malawi" pageId="9" pageNumber="460">Malawi</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
